Graph Coarsening
In Algorithm 2, we develop a hybrid graph coarsening
scheme which preserves global graph structural information
at different scales. Its two key parts, namely edge collaps-
ing and star collapsing, preserve ﬁrst-order proximity and
second-order proximity (Tang et al. 2015) respectively. First-
order proximity is concerned with preserving the observed
edges in the input graph, while second-order proximity isAlgorithm 2 GraphCoarsening( G)
