III. DATA ANALYSIS AND PREPROCESSING
In this section, we describe our proposed methods by first
introducing the existing and calculated features and then the
preprocessing techniques.
A. DATASET DESCRIPTION
The ‘‘Food Demand Forecasting’’ dataset [22] released by
Genpact, an American professional services firm, comprises
145 weeks’ worth of weekly orders for 50 distinct meals.
The data is divided into three files with a combined total of
about 4,50,000 entries and 15 features, which are explained
as follows:
1) Weekly Demand Data: includes the historical data of
the number of sales of a particular meal in a particular
center. The following details are included:
a) id: unique order ID associated.
b) week: week number (ranges from 1 to 145).
c) meal_id: unique ID associated with each meal.
d) center_id: unique ID associated with each fulfill-
ment center.
e) checkout_price: final price of the meal after all
the discount, taxes, and delivery charges.
f) base_price: base price of the meal as written in
the menu.
g) emailer_for_promotion: describes whether email
is sent for the promotion of the meal or not (0/1
implies no/yes).
