A. TERM WEIGHTING ON LOG DATA
The process of weighting log data involves two main steps.
First, the log history of the customer’s most recent access to
the app is extracted and the weight is assigned depending on
the app page visited. The daily difference between the point in
time when a customer departs and the date of access to the app
is calculated and weighted for each customer. The procedure
for this method is as follows.
