"Tongue Color Classification in TCM with Noisy
Labels via Confident-Learning-Assisted
Knowledge Distillation
LI Yanping1,2, ZHUO Li1,2, SUN Liangliang1,2, ZHANG Hui1,2,
LI Xiaoguang1,2, YANG Yang3,4, and WEI Wei3,4
(1. Beijing Key Laboratory of Computational Intelligence and Intelligent System,
Beijing University of Technology, Beijing 100124, China)
(2. Faculty of Information Technology, Beijing University of Technology, Beijing 100124, China)
(3. Department of Gastroenterology, Wangjing Hospital, China Academy of Chinese Medical Sciences, Beijing 100102, China)
(4. Beijing Key Laboratory of Traditional Chinese Medicine Treatment of Functional Gastrointestinal Diseases,
Beijing 100102, China)
 
   Abstract — Tongue color is an important tongue dia-
gnostic  index  for  traditional  Chinese  medicine  (TCM).
Due to the individual experience of TCM experts as well
as ambiguous boundaries among the tongue color categor-
ies,  there  often  exist  noisy  labels  in  annotated  samples.
Deep  neural  networks  trained  with  the  noisy  labeled
samples often have poor generalization capability because
they  easily  overfit  on  noisy  labels.  A  novel  framework
named  confident-learning-assisted  knowledge  distillation
(CLA-KD) is proposed for tongue color classification with
noisy labels. In this framework, the teacher network plays
two important roles. On the one hand, it performs confid-
ent learning to identify, cleanse and correct noisy labels.
On the other hand, it learns the knowledge from the clean
labels, which will then be transferred to the student net-
work  to  guide  its  training.  Moreover,  we  elaborately
design a teacher network in an ensemble manner, named
E-CA2-ResNet18, to  solve  the  unreliability  and  instabil-
ity  problem  resulted  from  the  insufficient  data  samples.
E-CA2-ResNet18  adopts  ResNet18  as  the  backbone,  and
integrates channel  attention  (CA)  mechanism  and  activ-
ate  or  not  activation  function  together,  which  facilitates
to  yield  a  better  performance.  The  experimental  results
on three  self-established  TCM  tongue  datasets  demon-
strate that, our proposed CLA-KD can obtain a superior
classification accuracy and good robustness with a lower
network model complexity, reaching 94.49%, 92.21%, 93.43%
on the three tongue image datasets, respectively.
   Key words — Traditional Chinese medicine, Tongue
color  classification, Confident  learning, Learning  fromnoisy  labels, Knowledge  distillation, Channel  attention
mechanism, ResNet18.
 I. Introduction
Traditional Chinese medicine (TCM) is one of the
ancient  Chinese  healing  systems.  Tongue  diagnosis
plays an important role in TCM. The diagnostic attrib-
utes  of  tongue,  including  tongue  color,  coating  color,
thickness, texture, humidity, shape, etc. is fundamental
for  TCM  diagnosis.  Among  them,  tongue  color  is  the
most intuitive and important one, which usually renders
four categories: light red, red, dark red, and purple. Due
to the individual experience of TCM experts as well as
ambiguous boundaries among the tongue color categor-
ies, there often exist noisy labels in annotated samples.
The  inconsistent  and  incorrect  labels  result  in  label
noise. Meanwhile, the number of labeled samples is usu-
ally scare because the collection and annotation of data
samples  are  time-consuming  and  expensive.  Therefore,
tongue color classification can essentially be regarded as
a  classification  problem  with  small-scale  data  samples
and noisy labels.
Tongue  color  classification  recently  made  a  giant
leap  with  the  advancements  of  deep  neural  networks
(DNNs). However, DNNs easily overfit on noisy labels, 
